1
00:01:35,719 --> 00:01:39,139
I thought you still had trauma from the crash.

2
00:01:39,139 --> 00:01:41,429
But you race like a madman?

3
00:01:41,429 --> 00:01:44,519
This is why trusting people is scary.

4
00:01:44,519 --> 00:01:48,134
You picked the wrong person.

5
00:01:50,592 --> 00:01:52,652
You thought I wouldn't know

6
00:01:52,652 --> 00:01:54,921
who you really are?

7
00:01:59,425 --> 00:02:02,162
Lee Sang Jae's mole.

8
00:02:02,162 --> 00:02:04,372
Comes and goes from the circuit,

9
00:02:04,372 --> 00:02:06,541
knows the key locker code by heart.

10
00:02:06,541 --> 00:02:09,294
Only Lee Sang Jae fits.

11
00:02:09,294 --> 00:02:10,323
That's not it...

12
00:02:10,323 --> 00:02:13,300
Foreign car, designer suit,

13
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,182
and a watch over fifty million?

14
00:02:16,182 --> 00:02:19,153
Whose pocket did all that come from?

15
00:02:27,210 --> 00:02:29,247
What did he order you to do?

16
00:02:29,981 --> 00:02:32,598
Stick by me and dig up dirt?

17
00:02:32,598 --> 00:02:34,694
Is this how you treat everyone?

18
00:02:34,694 --> 00:02:36,530
Behind Chairman Kang's back?

19
00:02:40,509 --> 00:02:43,970
Pain should refresh your memory.

20
00:02:52,337 --> 00:02:53,880
Come any closer

21
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,898
and I'll kill you.

22
00:02:58,885 --> 00:03:02,264
You're just like your old man after all.

23
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:09,813
That junk car that ruined my soccer career,

24
00:03:09,813 --> 00:03:11,210
I planned to ram it into something

25
00:03:11,210 --> 00:03:13,489
and total the damn thing.

26
00:03:13,489 --> 00:03:15,193
Wanted to see what made it so special,

27
00:03:15,193 --> 00:03:17,195
since it shattered my iron legs.

28
00:03:17,195 --> 00:03:19,990
One last ride before trashing it. So?

29
00:03:23,550 --> 00:03:25,344
But!

30
00:03:27,509 --> 00:03:29,849
I couldn't do it.

31
00:03:30,875 --> 00:03:34,000
A coward from a 300,000 won rooftop shack

32
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,398
doesn't have the guts to crash it!

33
00:03:40,093 --> 00:03:43,054
This knockoff watch,

34
00:03:43,054 --> 00:03:45,741
does it put me at a chaebol's level?

35
00:03:45,741 --> 00:03:48,993
Does any of this ease my anger?

36
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:58,361
That's really all of it?

37
00:04:09,456 --> 00:04:13,337
You think I handed you the port deal
just to get treated like this?

38
00:04:13,337 --> 00:04:14,753
Should I go to Lee Sang Jae

39
00:04:14,753 --> 00:04:17,172
and spill everything?

40
00:04:17,172 --> 00:04:20,091
You're the shady one.

41
00:04:27,509 --> 00:04:29,976
Not one apology, huh?

42
00:04:29,976 --> 00:04:32,137
I can't work with you.

43
00:04:32,137 --> 00:04:34,939
I'm not joining your office.

44
00:04:34,939 --> 00:04:35,969
What?

45
00:04:35,969 --> 00:04:38,446
I'm not taking your side.

46
00:04:38,446 --> 00:04:39,967
President Kang Jae Gyeong,

47
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:42,239
you've made a big mistake.

48
00:04:42,239 --> 00:04:44,340
Got it?

49
00:04:46,201 --> 00:04:47,800
I don't take chances

50
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:50,388
on unvetted people either.

51
00:05:12,218 --> 00:05:14,509
That witch.

52
00:05:14,509 --> 00:05:16,706
It cost 100 million won.

53
00:05:25,451 --> 00:05:28,634
Track Hwang Jun Hyeon's every move.

54
00:05:28,634 --> 00:05:30,688
Especially his ties to Lee Sang Jae.

55
00:05:30,688 --> 00:05:32,305
Yes, ma'am.

56
00:05:37,509 --> 00:05:40,480
I could finally breathe,

57
00:05:41,592 --> 00:05:44,358
and now I can't come here?

58
00:05:47,053 --> 00:05:48,763
What?

59
00:05:52,675 --> 00:05:55,205
Everyone's after me today.

60
00:05:55,205 --> 00:05:56,913
Who are you?

61
00:05:57,644 --> 00:05:59,385
Why do you have this?

62
00:05:59,385 --> 00:06:02,146
- Know what this is?
- Crown Palace suite key.

63
00:06:02,146 --> 00:06:05,822
That's what I'm asking, how?

64
00:06:05,822 --> 00:06:07,448
That's the chairman's safe house.

65
00:06:07,448 --> 00:06:08,944
Only I know about it.

66
00:06:08,944 --> 00:06:12,342
He keeps this card in his private safe.

67
00:06:12,342 --> 00:06:15,505
I took it out myself.

68
00:06:15,505 --> 00:06:18,326
You stole his cane from the hospital?

69
00:06:18,326 --> 00:06:19,885
You little punk!

70
00:06:19,885 --> 00:06:22,130
I had no choice.

71
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:23,832
It opens the safe.

72
00:06:23,832 --> 00:06:26,232
What did you do to our Chairman?

73
00:06:26,232 --> 00:06:28,068
Did you threaten him?

74
00:06:28,068 --> 00:06:30,655
Was the head-butt on purpose?

75
00:06:33,842 --> 00:06:37,208
You still don't know me?

76
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:40,816
Lee Sang Jae from Rose Villa, Heukseok-dong.

77
00:06:40,816 --> 00:06:42,408
What?

78
00:06:42,408 --> 00:06:45,153
Your mother's memorial is coming up?

79
00:06:45,153 --> 00:06:46,738
She was a kind woman.

80
00:06:46,738 --> 00:06:49,582
I was very fond of her.

81
00:06:51,319 --> 00:06:53,664
You dug into my background?

82
00:06:53,664 --> 00:06:55,219
You crazy punk!

83
00:06:55,219 --> 00:06:57,342
I am

84
00:06:57,342 --> 00:06:58,711
Chairman Kang.

85
00:06:58,711 --> 00:07:00,737
Kang Yong Ho!

86
00:07:01,461 --> 00:07:03,563
That's me.

87
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,425
When your mother passed,

88
00:07:07,425 --> 00:07:08,883
I went to the Baengnyeong burial site.

89
00:07:08,883 --> 00:07:12,447
How can you not know me?

90
00:07:14,307 --> 00:07:15,559
How would you know that?

91
00:07:15,559 --> 00:07:17,741
We share more than a few memories.

92
00:07:17,741 --> 00:07:20,230
A hurricane grounded the U.S. flight,

93
00:07:20,230 --> 00:07:23,425
and the groom and officiant nearly missed it.

94
00:07:23,425 --> 00:07:25,694
I was so nervous.

95
00:07:25,694 --> 00:07:28,818
I never officiated after your wedding.

96
00:07:30,531 --> 00:07:32,341
These days,

97
00:07:33,435 --> 00:07:35,954
I keep thinking of the Dubai hotel project.

98
00:07:35,954 --> 00:07:37,372
Sand kept pouring

99
00:07:37,372 --> 00:07:40,250
out of my nose and ears, no matter what I did.

100
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:42,210
Hold on...

101
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:44,926
Who told you that?

102
00:07:44,926 --> 00:07:45,964
That story

103
00:07:45,964 --> 00:07:48,816
isn't even in his autobiography.

104
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:52,428
I am Kang Yong Ho.

105
00:07:52,428 --> 00:07:54,222
You out of your mind?

106
00:07:54,222 --> 00:07:56,724
You're no Chairman Kang Yong Ho.

107
00:07:56,724 --> 00:07:58,842
You're clearly Hwang Jun Hyeon.

108
00:07:58,842 --> 00:08:00,103
Fair enough.

109
00:08:00,103 --> 00:08:01,592
Asking a materialist like you

110
00:08:01,592 --> 00:08:03,565
to believe in a soul swap

111
00:08:03,565 --> 00:08:06,542
is honestly absurd.

112
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:17,218
Work on your grip.

113
00:08:17,218 --> 00:08:20,389
You'll never beat me at arm wrestling.

114
00:08:23,418 --> 00:08:26,004
If you're truly my man,

115
00:08:26,004 --> 00:08:28,522
you'll find me soon.

116
00:08:52,197 --> 00:08:53,967
That can't be.

117
00:08:53,967 --> 00:08:57,552
He can't be the Chairman.

118
00:09:00,218 --> 00:09:02,473
My head hurts.

119
00:09:06,545 --> 00:09:08,842
That Sang Jae,

120
00:09:08,842 --> 00:09:11,691
his head must be spinning.

121
00:09:14,052 --> 00:09:16,847
Serves him right for not knowing me.

122
00:09:23,770 --> 00:09:24,980
[Crown Palace Hotel]

123
00:09:54,425 --> 00:09:56,235
Seriously.

124
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,800
I don't want to live here.

125
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:05,328
Why did I mention the rooftop?

126
00:10:13,986 --> 00:10:15,148
[Nurse Song]

127
00:10:17,051 --> 00:10:18,675
Yes, it's me.

128
00:10:18,675 --> 00:10:21,928
Your grandmother's tests are done.

129
00:10:23,496 --> 00:10:26,134
The dementia isn't severe,

130
00:10:26,134 --> 00:10:28,459
but she keeps asking for you.

131
00:10:28,459 --> 00:10:29,769
<i>The new surroundings</i>

132
00:10:29,769 --> 00:10:31,548
<i>seem to unsettle her.</i>

133
00:10:31,548 --> 00:10:34,298
<i>How about bringing her home?</i>

134
00:10:34,298 --> 00:10:36,676
Oh no, that's out of the question.

135
00:10:36,676 --> 00:10:39,140
You have a top-tier partner facility?

136
00:10:39,140 --> 00:10:40,176
Move her there for now.

137
00:10:40,176 --> 00:10:42,365
Tell her I'll visit soon.

138
00:10:46,509 --> 00:10:48,438
Right.

139
00:10:48,438 --> 00:10:51,541
Anywhere beats this dump.

140
00:10:53,668 --> 00:10:55,259
But wait,

141
00:10:55,259 --> 00:10:59,006
does this place even have a shower?

142
00:11:13,009 --> 00:11:16,482
So cold!

143
00:11:25,809 --> 00:11:27,627
Come on.

144
00:11:29,813 --> 00:11:34,037
I've never slept on the floor.

145
00:11:34,037 --> 00:11:35,944
Without my Hestuns mattress,

146
00:11:35,944 --> 00:11:39,297
I can't sleep a wink!

147
00:11:59,926 --> 00:12:01,611
I slept great.

148
00:12:02,429 --> 00:12:04,905
I wasn't supposed to.

149
00:12:13,717 --> 00:12:16,795
Why does changing take him forever?

150
00:12:16,795 --> 00:12:19,779
Showing your feelings is a habit too.

151
00:12:19,779 --> 00:12:21,879
Father, doesn't this gnaw at you?

152
00:12:21,879 --> 00:12:23,533
The Choiseong Trading shares under fake names,

153
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:26,092
plus the slush fund Director Song ran off with,

154
00:12:26,092 --> 00:12:28,497
we lost 500 billion won.

155
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:31,224
And we blew the port project too.

156
00:12:31,967 --> 00:12:34,179
How long must we trust Kang Jae Seong?

157
00:12:34,179 --> 00:12:36,296
Kang Jae Seong

158
00:12:36,296 --> 00:12:39,023
is bait to catch Choiseong.

159
00:12:40,884 --> 00:12:44,577
Soon we'll harpoon the whale.

160
00:12:45,425 --> 00:12:47,512
You didn't order yet?

161
00:12:47,512 --> 00:12:50,143
I already ordered the American breakfast.

162
00:12:50,143 --> 00:12:52,537
You have nerves of steel.

163
00:12:52,537 --> 00:12:56,666
Lost the port deal and still has an appetite.

164
00:12:59,051 --> 00:13:02,300
I don't show it,

165
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:04,595
but inside I'm burning up.

166
00:13:04,595 --> 00:13:07,193
Director Song's phone records,

167
00:13:07,193 --> 00:13:09,036
I'm digging through all of them.

168
00:13:09,036 --> 00:13:11,205
I'll find whoever's behind him

169
00:13:11,205 --> 00:13:14,629
and tear them limb from limb.

170
00:13:14,629 --> 00:13:17,254
You need proof to know?

171
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:20,563
I confirmed it. It's President Kang Jae Gyeong.

172
00:13:21,453 --> 00:13:24,218
He learned through Chief Ahn.

173
00:13:24,218 --> 00:13:27,798
<i>Did you really kill Director Song
to frame him for your slush fund?</i>

174
00:13:27,798 --> 00:13:32,383
Then stole the port deal too?

175
00:13:32,383 --> 00:13:33,964
I swear, I'll...

176
00:13:33,964 --> 00:13:36,784
Why trust that money to anyone?

177
00:13:36,784 --> 00:13:38,524
Keep your own people close.

178
00:13:38,524 --> 00:13:39,693
Eun Se,

179
00:13:39,693 --> 00:13:41,009
if not for Chairman Kang,

180
00:13:41,009 --> 00:13:43,363
would be running a Taeha subsidiary.

181
00:13:43,363 --> 00:13:44,997
What century is this?

182
00:13:44,997 --> 00:13:47,134
You don't cage a woman after marriage.

183
00:13:47,134 --> 00:13:50,092
Yet he hands his own daughter the chairmanship.

184
00:13:50,092 --> 00:13:51,662
Total hypocrisy.

185
00:13:51,662 --> 00:13:52,997
No.

186
00:13:52,997 --> 00:13:55,624
Kang Jae Gyeong becoming chairman
will never happen.

187
00:13:55,624 --> 00:13:56,877
Inside Choiseong,

188
00:13:56,877 --> 00:14:00,062
they're already calling her chairman.

189
00:14:03,275 --> 00:14:05,310
Father,

190
00:14:05,310 --> 00:14:07,945
aren't you being harsh on my husband?

191
00:14:08,930 --> 00:14:10,348
What's gotten into you?

192
00:14:10,348 --> 00:14:12,092
He did his best,
only to get stabbed in the back.

193
00:14:12,092 --> 00:14:14,218
It wasn't his ability.

194
00:14:14,218 --> 00:14:15,842
We're family, right?

195
00:14:15,842 --> 00:14:18,176
So trust him

196
00:14:18,176 --> 00:14:20,708
and back him up.

197
00:14:21,967 --> 00:14:23,653
Honey.

198
00:14:23,653 --> 00:14:25,193
This time,

199
00:14:25,193 --> 00:14:28,032
can you really beat your sister?

200
00:14:28,032 --> 00:14:29,742
Of course.

201
00:14:29,742 --> 00:14:32,675
I can't stand losing.

202
00:14:32,675 --> 00:14:34,414
GF Solutions.

203
00:14:34,414 --> 00:14:36,749
Land it yourself.

204
00:14:36,749 --> 00:14:37,503
Me?

205
00:14:37,503 --> 00:14:39,669
<i>We're acquiring GF Solutions,</i>

206
00:14:39,669 --> 00:14:42,005
<i>a battery tech company.</i>

207
00:14:42,005 --> 00:14:43,342
That's...

208
00:14:43,342 --> 00:14:45,884
the deal Jae Gyeong wants.

209
00:14:45,884 --> 00:14:47,383
Eye for an eye.

210
00:14:47,383 --> 00:14:49,800
Pay her back in kind.

211
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,765
Use Taeha's funds if needed.

212
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:53,759
I won't let my son-in-law

213
00:14:53,759 --> 00:14:56,218
look small.

214
00:14:56,218 --> 00:14:59,022
Thank you.

215
00:14:59,022 --> 00:15:00,957
I love you.

216
00:15:26,635 --> 00:15:28,928
He lives in Aejeong-dong.

217
00:15:28,928 --> 00:15:30,970
There's a grandmother with dementia,

218
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:32,592
but she's in a nursing facility.

219
00:15:32,592 --> 00:15:34,223
The car's a lease.

220
00:15:34,223 --> 00:15:37,045
The suit and watch look like knockoffs.

221
00:15:37,045 --> 00:15:38,061
Dig deeper.

222
00:15:38,061 --> 00:15:40,087
It could be a cover.

223
00:15:40,087 --> 00:15:43,108
Trust nothing until we know for sure.

224
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,834
Yes, ma'am.

225
00:15:45,634 --> 00:15:48,697
The company's leaning my way now.

226
00:15:48,697 --> 00:15:51,134
While we have the port deal,

227
00:15:51,134 --> 00:15:53,784
let's push the succession through.

228
00:15:53,784 --> 00:15:55,663
What about GF Solutions?

229
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:57,134
They took loans to expand,

230
00:15:57,134 --> 00:15:59,708
and now those loans are sinking them.

231
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:01,751
If they miss this week's notes,

232
00:16:01,751 --> 00:16:03,603
they're bankrupt.

233
00:16:04,329 --> 00:16:06,688
Call the bank presidents.

234
00:16:06,688 --> 00:16:09,150
Say I want a meeting.

235
00:16:19,592 --> 00:16:21,842
She's brutal.

236
00:16:21,842 --> 00:16:24,290
Who punches for an hour?

237
00:16:25,525 --> 00:16:29,670
<i>Jae Gyeong plans to bankrupt GF Solutions.</i>

238
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:34,364
Not on my watch.

239
00:16:41,259 --> 00:16:43,651
Manager Park, it's me.

240
00:16:43,651 --> 00:16:46,020
About yesterday's favor?

241
00:17:05,857 --> 00:17:07,931
[Materials Team 2]

242
00:17:21,247 --> 00:17:24,759
<i>I've got a tail, so I can't move.</i>

243
00:17:24,759 --> 00:17:26,675
<i>Pull some cash for me,</i>

244
00:17:26,675 --> 00:17:29,689
<i>around five billion won.</i>

245
00:17:57,759 --> 00:17:59,675
The young master

246
00:17:59,675 --> 00:18:02,581
trusts me completely.

247
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,940
Don't blow this.

248
00:18:10,550 --> 00:18:11,550
Carrying this over,

249
00:18:11,550 --> 00:18:13,592
I nearly had a heart attack.

250
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:15,719
A tail, seriously.

251
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:19,473
The chaebol life is a spectacle.

252
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:21,974
What's all this for?

253
00:18:21,974 --> 00:18:24,802
There's a company President Kang wants,

254
00:18:24,802 --> 00:18:26,897
and I'll help her get it.

255
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:28,685
An acquisition.

256
00:18:28,685 --> 00:18:31,500
[Mobility, Electric Vehicle]
The EV market's shaky, right?

257
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:32,800
With battery explosions,

258
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,213
demand's plummeting.

259
00:18:34,213 --> 00:18:36,440
The new battery tech that fixes that,

260
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:38,779
GF Solutions has it.

261
00:18:38,779 --> 00:18:41,675
It's almost ready for market.

262
00:18:41,675 --> 00:18:43,057
Why help her?

263
00:18:43,057 --> 00:18:44,331
If she succeeds,

264
00:18:44,331 --> 00:18:46,290
she rides the express elevator

265
00:18:46,290 --> 00:18:47,769
straight to chairman.

266
00:18:47,769 --> 00:18:49,894
Some money's missing.

267
00:18:50,509 --> 00:18:51,796
That's impossible.

268
00:18:51,796 --> 00:18:53,256
I didn't skim a single bill.

269
00:18:53,256 --> 00:18:55,525
It's all there.

270
00:18:56,843 --> 00:18:58,861
You're serious?

271
00:19:00,138 --> 00:19:01,506
I wouldn't even pick up

272
00:19:01,506 --> 00:19:03,426
a ten-won coin off the street.

273
00:19:03,426 --> 00:19:05,894
The rate's 1,465 won per dollar.

274
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:08,509
Five billion won converts

275
00:19:08,509 --> 00:19:11,585
to 3,415,021 dollars.

276
00:19:11,585 --> 00:19:13,902
In hundred dollar bills,

277
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:16,278
that's 34,150 notes.

278
00:19:16,278 --> 00:19:19,964
One, two, three, five, ten.

279
00:19:19,964 --> 00:19:21,963
A hundred per stack.

280
00:19:21,963 --> 00:19:24,720
That's 341 stacks...

281
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:27,924
plus 50 bills,

282
00:19:27,924 --> 00:19:29,583
3,415,000 dollars.

283
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:33,463
I'm honest to a fault.

284
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:35,356
I'm joking.

285
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:37,739
Young master,

286
00:19:37,739 --> 00:19:39,694
you scared me.

287
00:19:39,694 --> 00:19:40,884
Here.

288
00:19:40,884 --> 00:19:41,896
It's for your trouble.

289
00:19:41,896 --> 00:19:43,849
Send your kids in Canada some allowance.

290
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:45,009
Or maybe

291
00:19:45,009 --> 00:19:47,769
buy your wife a new bag.

292
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:49,812
This much?

293
00:19:49,812 --> 00:19:50,947
Thank you.

294
00:19:50,947 --> 00:19:53,142
Honestly,

295
00:19:53,142 --> 00:19:55,836
at first I didn't believe you were his son.

296
00:19:55,836 --> 00:19:58,884
The Chairman's looks are...

297
00:19:58,884 --> 00:20:00,475
nothing special.

298
00:20:00,475 --> 00:20:02,717
Big nose, small eyes,

299
00:20:02,717 --> 00:20:04,717
flat, broad face.

300
00:20:04,717 --> 00:20:06,995
But you, the looks,

301
00:20:06,995 --> 00:20:10,250
the brains, a total package.

302
00:20:13,690 --> 00:20:15,672
You talk

303
00:20:15,672 --> 00:20:18,924
way too much.

304
00:20:18,924 --> 00:20:20,802
I've got business with Casey,

305
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:24,530
so cover for me.

306
00:20:26,009 --> 00:20:27,825
Flat and broad?

307
00:20:33,259 --> 00:20:36,167
Why always with Casey...

308
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:40,107
Does he like her

309
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:43,716
more than me?

310
00:20:45,409 --> 00:20:48,162
CEO Kim, you know the economy.

311
00:20:48,162 --> 00:20:49,940
Loan reviews

312
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:51,333
aren't easy now.

313
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:54,310
There's nothing more we can do.

314
00:20:56,634 --> 00:20:59,524
The coffee's excellent.

315
00:21:01,176 --> 00:21:03,303
While we're here,

316
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:06,054
how about calling in GF Solutions' debt,
Mr. President?

317
00:21:06,054 --> 00:21:07,097
Then

318
00:21:07,097 --> 00:21:09,176
Choiseong Chemicals' payroll account

319
00:21:09,176 --> 00:21:11,650
stays with our bank, yes?

320
00:21:11,650 --> 00:21:13,634
You came all this way,

321
00:21:13,634 --> 00:21:15,023
of course.

322
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:18,401
The secretary told the cleaner
to make the office spotless.

323
00:21:18,401 --> 00:21:19,651
VIPs are coming.

324
00:21:19,651 --> 00:21:21,321
She's pulling in bank presidents

325
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:23,506
to choke GF Solutions' funding.

326
00:21:24,115 --> 00:21:25,784
<i>Yes, ma'am,</i>

327
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:27,828
<i>I'll take care of it.</i>

328
00:21:27,828 --> 00:21:29,118
[GF Solutions, CEO Kim Sang Do]

329
00:21:32,759 --> 00:21:34,583
Why's Joseong Bank's president here?

330
00:21:34,583 --> 00:21:37,158
What's she scheming now?

331
00:21:37,158 --> 00:21:39,005
For Choiseong Bio's new venture,

332
00:21:39,005 --> 00:21:41,174
I want Joseong Bank as a partner.

333
00:21:41,174 --> 00:21:44,544
So clear out the small loans first.

334
00:21:44,544 --> 00:21:46,721
You'll leave Kang Jae Gyeong alone?

335
00:21:46,721 --> 00:21:48,481
Push someone to the edge, offer a hand,

336
00:21:48,481 --> 00:21:50,742
nobody refuses.

337
00:21:52,176 --> 00:21:54,579
<i>That's how I taught her.</i>

338
00:21:54,579 --> 00:21:57,315
<i>Results matter.</i>

339
00:21:57,315 --> 00:22:01,800
<i>Just win, by any means.</i>

340
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:02,861
What about Kang Jae Seong?

341
00:22:02,861 --> 00:22:05,380
Golf meeting with Chairman Na this morning.

342
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:06,941
The driver says lately

343
00:22:06,941 --> 00:22:08,800
he's been glued to his father-in-law.

344
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,871
I figured he'd be tossed out
after losing the port deal.

345
00:22:11,871 --> 00:22:14,174
Heard of the sunk cost fallacy?

346
00:22:14,174 --> 00:22:17,101
Do you think I'm a fool?

347
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:20,009
You can't quit because of money already spent,

348
00:22:20,009 --> 00:22:21,800
so you take...

349
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,483
a bigger hit.

350
00:22:24,383 --> 00:22:26,800
Chairman Na will burn more cash

351
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,347
to stop Kang Jae Gyeong?

352
00:22:29,347 --> 00:22:31,683
And Jae Seong's gone mad too.

353
00:22:31,683 --> 00:22:34,060
[Acquisition Structure and Terms]
Chemicals' projected offer

354
00:22:34,060 --> 00:22:36,842
[GF Solutions Acquisition Proposal]
is under 100 billion won.

355
00:22:36,842 --> 00:22:37,855
Good.

356
00:22:37,855 --> 00:22:40,311
We'll put 100 billion won down.

357
00:22:40,311 --> 00:22:43,191
Sir, that's the minimum.

358
00:22:43,191 --> 00:22:46,411
We have funds locked for the port deal.
What's the issue?

359
00:22:46,411 --> 00:22:49,259
Trading funds into a Chemicals deal,

360
00:22:49,259 --> 00:22:52,410
how do you sell that?

361
00:22:52,410 --> 00:22:55,581
The chairman could change tomorrow.

362
00:22:55,581 --> 00:23:00,050
I'd walk through fire for you,
and you're stalling?

363
00:23:00,050 --> 00:23:01,310
Hold on.

364
00:23:01,310 --> 00:23:02,589
You're already

365
00:23:02,589 --> 00:23:05,255
siding with Kang Jae Gyeong?

366
00:23:05,255 --> 00:23:08,795
Are you scared I'll lose to her?

367
00:23:08,795 --> 00:23:12,307
Are you disrespecting me to my face?

368
00:23:12,307 --> 00:23:14,057
Of course not, sir.

369
00:23:14,057 --> 00:23:15,977
I said don't worry!

370
00:23:15,977 --> 00:23:18,146
I'll tap my father-in-law's money.

371
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:21,523
A hundred billion, a trillion, doesn't matter.
GF Solutions is mine.

372
00:23:21,523 --> 00:23:23,425
This time,

373
00:23:23,425 --> 00:23:26,759
I'll watch Kang Jae Gyeong

374
00:23:26,759 --> 00:23:29,226
cry tears of blood.

375
00:23:29,226 --> 00:23:30,242
Okay.

376
00:23:30,242 --> 00:23:31,634
Time to move.

377
00:23:31,634 --> 00:23:33,175
Right.

378
00:23:33,175 --> 00:23:34,938
Hold on.

379
00:23:34,938 --> 00:23:36,371
What's that outfit?

380
00:23:36,371 --> 00:23:38,041
A rich kid dressed like that?

381
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:39,118
What?

382
00:23:39,118 --> 00:23:40,335
It's...

383
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:42,779
a chameleon look to dodge the twins.

384
00:23:42,779 --> 00:23:44,840
You wouldn't get it.

385
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:45,528
Tacky.

386
00:23:45,528 --> 00:23:46,466
Cute.

387
00:23:46,466 --> 00:23:47,199
Tacky.

388
00:23:47,199 --> 00:23:48,635
This is cute.

389
00:23:48,635 --> 00:23:49,799
Just hurry up.

390
00:23:49,799 --> 00:23:51,529
What do you know?

391
00:24:22,759 --> 00:24:24,342
Filming a spy movie?

392
00:24:24,342 --> 00:24:25,922
So dramatic.

393
00:24:25,922 --> 00:24:28,148
You've never been tailed. Don't talk.

394
00:24:28,148 --> 00:24:30,133
Is it okay for both of us to be out?

395
00:24:30,133 --> 00:24:32,596
Two newbies missing will cause chaos.

396
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:35,058
Manager Park's covering for us.

397
00:24:36,139 --> 00:24:38,009
Hwang Jun Hyeon, Casey,

398
00:24:38,009 --> 00:24:42,163
is this how you work?

399
00:24:45,025 --> 00:24:47,527
If you can't handle the basics,

400
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:48,820
what then?

401
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:50,776
Until those files are done,

402
00:24:50,776 --> 00:24:53,971
don't even think of leaving!

403
00:24:53,971 --> 00:24:55,584
Water? No water either!

404
00:24:55,584 --> 00:24:56,745
I need to pee.

405
00:24:56,745 --> 00:24:59,329
No bathroom breaks.

406
00:24:59,329 --> 00:25:01,745
Those two, honestly.

407
00:25:01,745 --> 00:25:03,584
What happened?

408
00:25:03,584 --> 00:25:05,372
You scolded Casey too.

409
00:25:05,372 --> 00:25:07,093
Why handle it yourself?

410
00:25:07,093 --> 00:25:08,573
- I can teach them.
- No.

411
00:25:08,573 --> 00:25:12,177
I'll handle those two personally.

412
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:14,593
Otherwise you all get stressed.

413
00:25:14,593 --> 00:25:15,800
Manager,

414
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,512
so sweet.

415
00:25:17,512 --> 00:25:18,934
Back to your desks.

416
00:25:18,934 --> 00:25:20,552
Move it!

417
00:25:20,552 --> 00:25:24,789
Coddling them spoils them.

418
00:25:27,517 --> 00:25:31,106
Director, what brings you here?

419
00:25:31,106 --> 00:25:32,988
Where's Hwang Jun Hyeon?

420
00:25:32,988 --> 00:25:34,565
What's this about?

421
00:25:34,565 --> 00:25:35,699
Should I get him?

422
00:25:35,699 --> 00:25:36,787
He's not in there.

423
00:25:36,787 --> 00:25:38,537
- Excuse me?
- What do you mean?

424
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:40,704
He might have stepped out...

425
00:25:40,704 --> 00:25:42,207
- What?
- No, that's not it,

426
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:43,667
the incident report...

427
00:25:43,667 --> 00:25:45,959
If he sorts files there,

428
00:25:45,959 --> 00:25:47,671
he can't focus...

429
00:25:47,671 --> 00:25:48,767
What are you saying?

430
00:25:48,767 --> 00:25:50,048
So is he here or not?

431
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:51,342
He's here...

432
00:25:51,342 --> 00:25:52,592
Not... here...

433
00:25:52,592 --> 00:25:54,732
Come on.

434
00:25:54,732 --> 00:25:57,238
- His desk?
- This way.

435
00:26:04,521 --> 00:26:06,134
[Relocation of Port Businesses
to Gangwon Province]

436
00:26:06,134 --> 00:26:08,583
How could this be...

437
00:26:10,692 --> 00:26:13,738
Director, tell me what this is about,

438
00:26:13,738 --> 00:26:15,282
and I'll pass it to Jun Hyeon

439
00:26:15,282 --> 00:26:18,176
as fast as possible.

440
00:26:19,967 --> 00:26:22,247
Get back to work. It's fine.

441
00:26:22,247 --> 00:26:24,009
I'm losing it.

442
00:26:24,009 --> 00:26:25,917
Why is everything

443
00:26:25,917 --> 00:26:27,727
falling apart?

444
00:26:29,586 --> 00:26:31,322
Young master,

445
00:26:31,322 --> 00:26:33,425
we have an emergency.

446
00:26:33,425 --> 00:26:34,422
[To: Managing Director Lee Sang Jae]

447
00:26:39,514 --> 00:26:40,528
[Kang Yong Ho]

448
00:26:45,473 --> 00:26:46,480
[I hereby order this]

449
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:48,028
[From this moment on...
there will be no bloodline succession]

450
00:26:51,860 --> 00:26:53,624
[I hereby order this]

451
00:26:53,624 --> 00:26:55,302
[An undervalued region
with easy access to Seoul]

452
00:27:00,368 --> 00:27:03,955
<i>Meet me at our usual spot at ten.</i>

453
00:27:03,955 --> 00:27:06,140
<i>Watch for tails.</i>

454
00:27:14,369 --> 00:27:16,278
Chairman...

455
00:27:25,519 --> 00:27:28,619
Who's that wistful text for?

456
00:27:29,467 --> 00:27:30,524
Who is it?

457
00:27:30,524 --> 00:27:31,952
Someone.

458
00:27:31,952 --> 00:27:34,127
Someone I must meet.

459
00:27:35,821 --> 00:27:37,755
Girlfriend?

460
00:27:42,092 --> 00:27:44,538
I'll change fast. Wait here.

461
00:27:44,538 --> 00:27:46,264
Hold on,

462
00:27:46,872 --> 00:27:50,372
I need the bathroom too.

463
00:27:50,372 --> 00:27:51,967
Number two?

464
00:27:51,967 --> 00:27:53,813
Number one.

465
00:27:58,604 --> 00:28:00,278
That way!

466
00:28:00,929 --> 00:28:03,114
Stay out of sight.

467
00:28:08,962 --> 00:28:10,099
Housekeeper Jo!

468
00:28:10,099 --> 00:28:12,206
Why is this so salty?

469
00:28:16,484 --> 00:28:17,937
Kids need low-sugar,

470
00:28:17,937 --> 00:28:20,965
low-sodium meals. You don't know?

471
00:28:24,784 --> 00:28:26,258
It's not that salty.

472
00:28:26,258 --> 00:28:28,479
Don't taste mine. Gross.

473
00:28:28,479 --> 00:28:30,290
Make it again.

474
00:28:30,290 --> 00:28:32,092
I'm your grandmother. So what?

475
00:28:32,092 --> 00:28:33,418
No grandmother of mine.

476
00:28:33,418 --> 00:28:36,671
We share no blood with you.

477
00:28:36,671 --> 00:28:39,843
Il Jun, I changed your diapers,

478
00:28:39,843 --> 00:28:42,512
made your baby food, raised you.

479
00:28:42,512 --> 00:28:43,762
Where are your manners?

480
00:28:43,762 --> 00:28:46,097
That's the housekeeper's job.

481
00:28:46,097 --> 00:28:47,767
Are you scolding me?

482
00:28:47,767 --> 00:28:49,639
I'll tell my mom.

483
00:28:49,639 --> 00:28:52,147
How old are you,

484
00:28:52,147 --> 00:28:53,680
running to mommy?

485
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:56,592
You're in grade school. Grow up.

486
00:28:56,592 --> 00:28:57,785
Housekeeper Jo,

487
00:28:57,785 --> 00:28:58,818
water,

488
00:28:58,818 --> 00:29:01,156
not hot, not cold.

489
00:29:01,156 --> 00:29:03,408
Use your judgment.

490
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:04,449
Housekeeper Jo.

491
00:29:04,449 --> 00:29:06,620
Bring my soup first!

492
00:29:07,550 --> 00:29:10,264
Those brats.

493
00:29:17,092 --> 00:29:18,713
Our driver?

494
00:29:18,713 --> 00:29:20,379
Nobody mentioned a new one.

495
00:29:20,379 --> 00:29:22,467
Your grandfather sent me.

496
00:29:22,467 --> 00:29:23,530
What?

497
00:29:23,530 --> 00:29:25,507
Grandpa's basically dying.

498
00:29:25,507 --> 00:29:28,408
He's right behind you.

499
00:29:29,224 --> 00:29:30,238
You're messing with us?

500
00:29:30,238 --> 00:29:32,102
I'm not.

501
00:29:32,102 --> 00:29:34,342
Yes, Chairman.

502
00:29:34,342 --> 00:29:35,981
Min Il Jun,

503
00:29:35,981 --> 00:29:38,134
last year you broke his prized vase.

504
00:29:38,134 --> 00:29:40,711
Did you forget he forgave you?

505
00:29:41,577 --> 00:29:43,550
Oh, really, Chairman?

506
00:29:43,550 --> 00:29:44,783
Kang Yi Jun,

507
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:47,997
you took the gold turtle from his study, right?

508
00:29:47,997 --> 00:29:49,887
That's what he's saying.

509
00:29:54,342 --> 00:29:57,963
He's watching every move.

510
00:29:57,963 --> 00:30:01,018
His body's in bed, but his soul is right here,

511
00:30:02,884 --> 00:30:05,445
right beside you.

512
00:30:06,550 --> 00:30:08,967
Call Grandma "housekeeper" again,

513
00:30:08,967 --> 00:30:11,232
and he'll haunt you nightly.

514
00:30:11,232 --> 00:30:13,937
Use the right title and show respect.

515
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:15,509
If not,

516
00:30:15,509 --> 00:30:19,734
the moment he wakes, your shares are gone.

517
00:30:19,734 --> 00:30:21,544
Got it?

518
00:30:26,176 --> 00:30:28,634
This meeting never happened.

519
00:30:29,387 --> 00:30:30,392
Answer me.

520
00:30:30,392 --> 00:30:32,581
- Yes.
- Yes.

521
00:30:32,581 --> 00:30:34,348
Go.

522
00:30:37,967 --> 00:30:40,104
Nobody's dying.

523
00:30:46,092 --> 00:30:49,383
If she's your girlfriend, just say so.

524
00:30:49,383 --> 00:30:52,259
"Someone I must meet."

525
00:30:52,259 --> 00:30:55,119
Like I even care.

526
00:31:14,498 --> 00:31:16,724
Hwang Jun Hyeon?

527
00:31:23,407 --> 00:31:26,216
Grandma, thank you for the meal.

528
00:31:26,216 --> 00:31:28,512
Always grateful.

529
00:31:32,180 --> 00:31:35,034
We'll be on our way.

530
00:31:41,064 --> 00:31:43,485
What's gotten into those brats?

531
00:31:43,485 --> 00:31:44,736
Right?

532
00:31:44,736 --> 00:31:46,926
When did you...

533
00:31:46,926 --> 00:31:49,114
And that outfit?

534
00:31:49,114 --> 00:31:50,325
How do I look? Super cute, right?

535
00:31:50,325 --> 00:31:53,161
Totally adorable? Love at first sight, right?

536
00:31:53,161 --> 00:31:55,956
Your father would lose it.

537
00:31:55,956 --> 00:31:57,639
Asking where you're going like that.

538
00:31:57,639 --> 00:31:59,099
Where do you think you're going?

539
00:31:59,099 --> 00:32:00,119
Oh, please.

540
00:32:00,119 --> 00:32:02,502
Why is that skirt so short?
Shoulders all hanging out.

541
00:32:02,502 --> 00:32:04,239
You call that clothes? It's a rag.

542
00:32:04,239 --> 00:32:05,338
I said dress with class,

543
00:32:05,338 --> 00:32:07,024
not like a tramp.

544
00:32:07,024 --> 00:32:10,011
It looks fine to me!

545
00:32:10,011 --> 00:32:12,613
If it's bad, I'll change.

546
00:32:13,930 --> 00:32:16,351
Forget it. No time. Just let's go.

547
00:32:40,740 --> 00:32:41,926
What?

548
00:32:41,926 --> 00:32:43,170
Taking a nap?

549
00:32:43,170 --> 00:32:44,425
I said no time.

550
00:32:44,425 --> 00:32:46,674
What do I do with you?

551
00:32:46,674 --> 00:32:48,092
I'm going!

552
00:32:48,092 --> 00:32:50,594
No need to nag.

553
00:32:50,594 --> 00:32:52,914
You ride shotgun.

554
00:32:52,914 --> 00:32:55,531
I'm your secretary today.

555
00:32:59,342 --> 00:33:00,729
Why does he

556
00:33:00,729 --> 00:33:02,914
keep getting to me?

557
00:33:08,236 --> 00:33:10,028
You promised the extension.

558
00:33:10,028 --> 00:33:11,917
How can you flip on me now?

559
00:33:11,917 --> 00:33:13,241
I'm begging you.

560
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:16,300
If I can't cover this week, I'm done.

561
00:33:16,300 --> 00:33:18,634
Hello?

562
00:33:18,634 --> 00:33:20,807
Come on!

563
00:33:28,965 --> 00:33:30,634
Why are you out here, not working?

564
00:33:30,634 --> 00:33:31,843
We can't take it anymore.

565
00:33:31,843 --> 00:33:34,613
It's been three months. Pay us, then work us.

566
00:33:34,613 --> 00:33:37,274
If we stop, what about the orders?

567
00:33:37,274 --> 00:33:38,600
The loan was denied.

568
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,313
What orders?

569
00:33:40,313 --> 00:33:42,294
Are you killing us to save the company?

570
00:33:42,294 --> 00:33:44,397
This is too much.

571
00:33:44,397 --> 00:33:46,594
- Let's go.
- Cut me some slack.

572
00:33:46,594 --> 00:33:48,816
Just one more time.

573
00:33:48,816 --> 00:33:51,414
We have to deliver.

574
00:33:51,414 --> 00:33:53,675
Three months!

575
00:33:53,675 --> 00:33:56,176
Are we volunteers?

576
00:33:56,176 --> 00:33:57,911
You're just giving us the runaround.

577
00:33:57,911 --> 00:34:00,346
What is this, a joke?

578
00:34:01,329 --> 00:34:03,683
CEO Kim Sang Do?

579
00:34:10,342 --> 00:34:11,923
At your demand,

580
00:34:11,923 --> 00:34:13,218
we expanded the lines,

581
00:34:13,218 --> 00:34:14,886
took loans we couldn't afford.

582
00:34:14,886 --> 00:34:18,098
Now you're cutting orders in half?

583
00:34:18,098 --> 00:34:20,073
A big project tied up our funds,

584
00:34:20,073 --> 00:34:22,549
so cash is tight.

585
00:34:22,549 --> 00:34:24,661
So here's the thing.

586
00:34:29,276 --> 00:34:31,594
[Choiseong Chemicals GF Solutions
Acquisition Proposal]

587
00:34:32,237 --> 00:34:34,061
Sell us the company

588
00:34:34,061 --> 00:34:35,757
for 80 billion won.

589
00:34:38,243 --> 00:34:39,536
What are you doing?

590
00:34:39,536 --> 00:34:43,454
35 percent of your sales
is Choiseong Chemicals.

591
00:34:43,454 --> 00:34:45,550
You can't make payroll.

592
00:34:45,550 --> 00:34:47,092
If we cut ties,

593
00:34:47,092 --> 00:34:50,211
you'll sell for less.

594
00:34:50,211 --> 00:34:53,133
Your life's work ending like that.

595
00:34:53,133 --> 00:34:55,485
Is that what you want?

596
00:34:59,014 --> 00:35:00,724
I'm

597
00:35:00,724 --> 00:35:03,564
here to help you.

598
00:35:03,564 --> 00:35:05,453
Not your enemy.

599
00:35:08,926 --> 00:35:12,627
CEO Kim, you in there?

600
00:35:14,592 --> 00:35:17,365
Choiseong keeps hassling me.

601
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:18,658
What do you think this is,

602
00:35:18,658 --> 00:35:21,761
mackerel at a fish market?

603
00:35:24,231 --> 00:35:26,057
I know.

604
00:35:26,875 --> 00:35:30,545
Kang Jae Gyeong came in to lowball you.

605
00:35:30,545 --> 00:35:31,884
But

606
00:35:31,884 --> 00:35:36,150
she's the one who blocked your loans.

607
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:40,764
Cornered you to take the company.

608
00:35:40,764 --> 00:35:41,848
Are you serious?

609
00:35:41,848 --> 00:35:43,673
Exposing my own sister's dirt,

610
00:35:43,673 --> 00:35:45,811
why would I do this?

611
00:35:45,811 --> 00:35:47,796
A company this good

612
00:35:47,796 --> 00:35:49,773
shouldn't be treated like that.

613
00:35:49,773 --> 00:35:53,259
Better me than Kang Jae Gyeong,

614
00:35:53,259 --> 00:35:54,966
[GF Solutions Acquisition Proposal]
who has no clue of its worth.

615
00:35:55,734 --> 00:35:59,340
100 billion won wouldn't even be enough.

616
00:36:00,259 --> 00:36:02,760
100 billion won?

617
00:36:05,717 --> 00:36:06,790
Get out now!

618
00:36:06,790 --> 00:36:08,433
Out!

619
00:36:11,717 --> 00:36:13,729
No.

620
00:36:14,962 --> 00:36:16,508
Got a hole-in-the-wall

621
00:36:16,508 --> 00:36:18,984
and acts so high and mighty.

622
00:36:21,134 --> 00:36:22,675
Call my father-in-law.

623
00:36:22,675 --> 00:36:25,616
Tell him his only son-in-law needs more.

624
00:36:29,163 --> 00:36:31,270
Did you check Chemicals' funds?

625
00:36:31,270 --> 00:36:33,775
The most they can move

626
00:36:33,775 --> 00:36:35,603
is 100 billion won.

627
00:36:35,603 --> 00:36:38,446
So if it goes over 100 billion?

628
00:36:38,446 --> 00:36:40,113
<i>It'll be tough.</i>

629
00:36:40,113 --> 00:36:42,051
They're short on cash.

630
00:36:42,051 --> 00:36:45,537
And the executives will push back hard.

631
00:36:45,537 --> 00:36:48,431
Let's push her to the edge.

632
00:36:50,236 --> 00:36:53,352
Make her drain every slush fund.

633
00:37:07,129 --> 00:37:10,799
Bargain over a dead cow,
you think you'll get a fair price?

634
00:37:11,580 --> 00:37:14,483
Is there a rumor we tanked?

635
00:37:14,483 --> 00:37:16,318
I'm not selling.

636
00:37:16,318 --> 00:37:17,984
Leave.

637
00:37:17,984 --> 00:37:19,467
If it's a dead cow,

638
00:37:19,467 --> 00:37:21,068
I'll go down with it.

639
00:37:21,068 --> 00:37:24,004
That only helps Choiseong.

640
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:26,592
Close shop,

641
00:37:26,592 --> 00:37:28,880
and they'll steal it.

642
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:30,665
Who are you?

643
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:32,725
Manager Hwang.

644
00:37:35,259 --> 00:37:37,506
[Smile Investment]
I know a M&A wizard

645
00:37:37,506 --> 00:37:40,091
who revives dead firms.

646
00:37:40,091 --> 00:37:42,485
Care to meet her?

647
00:37:44,347 --> 00:37:46,155
This way.

648
00:37:47,808 --> 00:37:49,248
Our CEO uses this as her office

649
00:37:49,248 --> 00:37:51,225
and her home.

650
00:37:51,225 --> 00:37:52,646
It's spacious enough

651
00:37:52,646 --> 00:37:55,127
for a quiet talk.

652
00:37:55,127 --> 00:37:57,227
Oh my...

653
00:37:58,068 --> 00:37:59,148
Hi, welcome.

654
00:37:59,148 --> 00:38:02,697
Sorry to bring you here on such short notice.

655
00:38:02,697 --> 00:38:04,389
What?

656
00:38:04,389 --> 00:38:06,576
I just got back from the States.

657
00:38:06,576 --> 00:38:09,120
I'm Casey Kang, M&A specialist.

658
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:11,305
Yeah.

659
00:38:11,998 --> 00:38:13,708
Good work, Manager Hwang.

660
00:38:13,708 --> 00:38:15,549
Have a seat.

661
00:38:15,549 --> 00:38:16,650
Whiskey?

662
00:38:16,650 --> 00:38:18,259
I invested in this distillery.

663
00:38:18,259 --> 00:38:20,926
The taste is solid.

664
00:38:20,926 --> 00:38:23,151
I'll pour.

665
00:38:27,656 --> 00:38:29,250
This is my dad's too,

666
00:38:29,250 --> 00:38:30,892
and you're acting like it's yours.

667
00:38:30,892 --> 00:38:33,369
It's strategy.

668
00:38:34,563 --> 00:38:36,882
Could be ours someday.

669
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:40,134
<i>Could be ours someday.</i>

670
00:38:40,134 --> 00:38:42,462
<i>Could be ours someday.</i>

671
00:38:56,092 --> 00:38:57,695
I'll skip the drink.

672
00:38:57,695 --> 00:38:59,893
How do you know my company?

673
00:38:59,893 --> 00:39:02,153
Hard to know outside the field.

674
00:39:02,153 --> 00:39:03,717
Didn't he mention?

675
00:39:03,717 --> 00:39:06,175
I don't waste money.

676
00:39:06,175 --> 00:39:07,220
You bet.

677
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:08,752
Never.

678
00:39:08,752 --> 00:39:11,176
Not a dollar, not a cent.

679
00:39:11,176 --> 00:39:13,057
But

680
00:39:13,057 --> 00:39:15,411
for GF Solutions,

681
00:39:17,967 --> 00:39:20,208
she's putting in five billion won.

682
00:39:21,592 --> 00:39:24,253
Use it to restart the factory.

683
00:39:25,412 --> 00:39:27,491
A businessman taking unmarked cash?

684
00:39:27,491 --> 00:39:29,759
Ever heard of that?

685
00:39:31,147 --> 00:39:32,514
Name your terms.

686
00:39:32,514 --> 00:39:33,788
You're an investor.

687
00:39:33,788 --> 00:39:35,707
There must be conditions.

688
00:39:35,707 --> 00:39:38,126
GF Solutions shares,

689
00:39:38,126 --> 00:39:39,769
30 percent.

690
00:39:44,675 --> 00:39:46,800
You're worse than Choiseong.

691
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,155
Trying to steal my company.

692
00:39:48,155 --> 00:39:50,472
The solid-state battery tech,

693
00:39:50,472 --> 00:39:52,265
I'll get you a fair price.

694
00:39:52,265 --> 00:39:53,850
Sell for 300 billion won

695
00:39:53,850 --> 00:39:55,785
to Choiseong Chemicals.

696
00:40:04,986 --> 00:40:07,196
Choiseong isn't dumb.

697
00:40:08,072 --> 00:40:10,793
They'd never pay that.

698
00:40:10,793 --> 00:40:12,509
If the deal falls through

699
00:40:12,509 --> 00:40:14,955
and they cut ties,

700
00:40:14,955 --> 00:40:16,626
I'm finished.

701
00:40:16,626 --> 00:40:18,811
We'll make them buy it.

702
00:40:18,811 --> 00:40:21,134
But you must

703
00:40:21,134 --> 00:40:22,467
trust us completely.

704
00:40:22,467 --> 00:40:25,440
And don't turn on us.

705
00:40:30,105 --> 00:40:31,738
Well,

706
00:40:32,550 --> 00:40:34,657
if that's possible.

707
00:40:39,688 --> 00:40:41,634
What

708
00:40:41,634 --> 00:40:43,773
do I do?

709
00:40:43,773 --> 00:40:45,623
Let's draw up the contract.

710
00:40:45,623 --> 00:40:47,628
Stop the bankruptcy first.

711
00:40:48,463 --> 00:40:51,883
The factory has to run to attract bees.

712
00:40:59,372 --> 00:41:03,003
I have somewhere to be.

713
00:41:03,003 --> 00:41:04,812
At this hour?

714
00:41:05,467 --> 00:41:06,534
Where?

715
00:41:06,534 --> 00:41:08,258
With who?

716
00:41:08,258 --> 00:41:10,398
That's private.

717
00:41:16,842 --> 00:41:18,477
Has to be a date.

718
00:41:18,477 --> 00:41:19,967
He clearly has a girlfriend.

719
00:41:19,967 --> 00:41:21,746
Hey.

720
00:41:22,355 --> 00:41:24,900
That's harsh.

721
00:41:24,900 --> 00:41:26,759
What?

722
00:41:26,759 --> 00:41:28,419
I mean...

723
00:42:19,303 --> 00:42:20,969
Sorry I'm late.

724
00:42:20,969 --> 00:42:23,766
Why stand out here? You'll catch a cold.

725
00:42:25,675 --> 00:42:28,563
I wanted to see you sooner.

726
00:42:29,342 --> 00:42:32,300
Have you been well, sir?

727
00:42:32,300 --> 00:42:34,803
How could I be, without you?

728
00:42:34,803 --> 00:42:36,487
You know that.

729
00:42:39,884 --> 00:42:41,784
Sir.

730
00:42:42,933 --> 00:42:46,356
Watching all that happen,

731
00:42:46,356 --> 00:42:49,455
how you must have suffered.

732
00:42:49,455 --> 00:42:52,864
I should have known sooner.

733
00:42:52,864 --> 00:42:55,800
I couldn't help you at all,

734
00:42:56,467 --> 00:42:57,742
and I'm sorry.

735
00:42:57,742 --> 00:43:00,342
Don't apologize.

736
00:43:00,342 --> 00:43:01,884
After my kids stabbed me in the back,

737
00:43:01,884 --> 00:43:05,183
I thought life was cruel,

738
00:43:07,300 --> 00:43:09,645
but you give me strength.

739
00:43:10,518 --> 00:43:12,061
Thank you,

740
00:43:12,061 --> 00:43:13,842
for proving my life

741
00:43:13,842 --> 00:43:16,736
wasn't wasted.

742
00:43:21,467 --> 00:43:23,717
Come on,

743
00:43:23,717 --> 00:43:25,703
get up now.

744
00:43:31,026 --> 00:43:32,935
Hey.

745
00:43:33,904 --> 00:43:35,963
It's been a while.

746
00:43:38,467 --> 00:43:41,113
How did I fall like this?

747
00:43:41,113 --> 00:43:43,387
My knees gave out.

748
00:43:44,134 --> 00:43:45,165
Hold on.

749
00:43:45,165 --> 00:43:48,300
Isn't your second graduating college soon?

750
00:43:48,300 --> 00:43:52,230
He'd begged to join Choiseong
since he was this tall.

751
00:43:53,381 --> 00:43:55,191
Remember?

752
00:43:56,259 --> 00:44:00,675
This guy's a new hire,

753
00:44:00,675 --> 00:44:03,176
and his head's all over the place.

754
00:44:03,176 --> 00:44:05,253
Needs extra attention.

755
00:44:05,253 --> 00:44:06,786
Pull it together!

756
00:44:11,817 --> 00:44:13,601
It's raining.

757
00:44:24,842 --> 00:44:27,457
Your appetite...

758
00:44:27,457 --> 00:44:30,335
I'm hungry every five minutes.

759
00:44:30,335 --> 00:44:31,863
Want to feel it?

760
00:44:31,863 --> 00:44:33,672
My whole body's like a racehorse.

761
00:44:33,672 --> 00:44:35,731
Goodness.

762
00:44:37,968 --> 00:44:40,176
Being young

763
00:44:40,176 --> 00:44:42,488
really is something.

764
00:44:43,467 --> 00:44:45,867
I can protect Choiseong.

765
00:44:47,060 --> 00:44:48,748
Meanwhile,

766
00:44:49,383 --> 00:44:52,190
you recovered President Kang's slush fund

767
00:44:52,190 --> 00:44:53,984
and snatched the port project,

768
00:44:53,984 --> 00:44:56,218
all alone.

769
00:44:56,218 --> 00:44:57,719
I had no idea.

770
00:44:57,719 --> 00:44:59,904
I wasn't alone.

771
00:44:59,904 --> 00:45:02,518
Bang Geul's grown up quite a bit.

772
00:45:02,518 --> 00:45:03,743
Don't tell me...

773
00:45:03,743 --> 00:45:05,784
she knows too?

774
00:45:05,784 --> 00:45:08,212
That you're in Hwang Jun Hyeon's body.

775
00:45:09,583 --> 00:45:11,820
Keep it quiet, for now.

776
00:45:16,717 --> 00:45:17,756
Sang Jae.

777
00:45:17,756 --> 00:45:19,400
Yes.

778
00:45:20,926 --> 00:45:23,738
I have much to gain ahead,

779
00:45:24,347 --> 00:45:26,266
and much to throw away.

780
00:45:26,266 --> 00:45:29,308
That's why you're acting chairman.

781
00:45:29,308 --> 00:45:30,979
Sir.

782
00:45:30,979 --> 00:45:32,898
Just give the order.

783
00:45:32,898 --> 00:45:34,563
What do you need, sir?

784
00:45:34,563 --> 00:45:35,800
All right.

785
00:45:35,800 --> 00:45:37,710
First...

786
00:45:40,947 --> 00:45:43,344
Drive me to the office.

787
00:45:48,914 --> 00:45:50,947
[12:07 AM, February 5]

788
00:45:50,947 --> 00:45:52,308
What kind of place

789
00:45:52,308 --> 00:45:56,210
makes people work this late every night?

790
00:45:56,210 --> 00:45:57,247
I'm wiped.

791
00:45:57,247 --> 00:45:59,090
<i>12:07 a.m.</i>

792
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:01,025
<i>Hwang Jun Hyeon, off the clock.</i>

793
00:46:03,547 --> 00:46:05,279
Tired.

794
00:46:05,967 --> 00:46:08,032
So tired.

795
00:46:13,511 --> 00:46:16,833
Tomorrow, I'll put you clowns to work.

796
00:46:22,092 --> 00:46:23,490
Still no word from CEO Kim?

797
00:46:23,490 --> 00:46:26,391
He's ignored my calls all morning.

798
00:46:26,391 --> 00:46:27,869
Take me to GF Solutions.

799
00:46:27,869 --> 00:46:29,111
Right away.

800
00:46:29,111 --> 00:46:31,222
Morning, sis.

801
00:46:33,176 --> 00:46:34,459
You okay?

802
00:46:34,459 --> 00:46:36,978
Did something go wrong?

803
00:46:41,092 --> 00:46:44,848
Why the sour face?

804
00:46:44,848 --> 00:46:47,697
The fun hasn't even started.

805
00:46:55,259 --> 00:46:58,024
There she is, my little sister.

806
00:46:58,024 --> 00:47:00,443
CEO Kim.

807
00:47:00,443 --> 00:47:03,196
I couldn't reach you.

808
00:47:03,196 --> 00:47:05,715
I couldn't find my phone.

809
00:47:08,996 --> 00:47:10,800
Is this it?

810
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:12,202
Yes, that's it.

811
00:47:12,202 --> 00:47:15,270
It kept buzzing under my butt,

812
00:47:15,270 --> 00:47:18,092
I thought I was sitting on a massage chair.

813
00:47:18,092 --> 00:47:20,354
Did you call a lot?

814
00:47:22,717 --> 00:47:25,677
Choiseong's gentleman will take his leave.

815
00:47:25,677 --> 00:47:27,259
Yes.

816
00:47:27,259 --> 00:47:28,727
Stamp the acquisition proposal,

817
00:47:28,727 --> 00:47:30,634
and let's hit the course soon.

818
00:47:30,634 --> 00:47:32,383
See you.

819
00:47:32,383 --> 00:47:34,077
Take care.

820
00:47:45,345 --> 00:47:47,218
Don't tell me

821
00:47:47,218 --> 00:47:49,659
you're going with Trading.

822
00:47:49,659 --> 00:47:51,025
What,

823
00:47:51,025 --> 00:47:52,804
is that a problem?

824
00:47:54,550 --> 00:47:57,471
Should I cut all ties with you right now?

825
00:47:57,471 --> 00:47:59,336
Let's see if you can dodge bankruptcy.

826
00:47:59,336 --> 00:48:01,016
Why would I go bankrupt?

827
00:48:01,016 --> 00:48:04,424
The factory's running just fine.

828
00:48:04,424 --> 00:48:05,825
Why so surprised?

829
00:48:05,825 --> 00:48:07,219
Were you planning to block

830
00:48:07,219 --> 00:48:09,404
every one of our bank loans again?

831
00:48:12,884 --> 00:48:15,300
Are you really buying Jae Seong's story?

832
00:48:15,300 --> 00:48:16,637
Anyway,

833
00:48:16,637 --> 00:48:18,704
I'm not selling to you,

834
00:48:20,574 --> 00:48:22,893
unless you beat Trading's offer.

835
00:48:27,383 --> 00:48:29,674
Name your price.

836
00:48:30,898 --> 00:48:33,458
Put yourself in my shoes,

837
00:48:33,458 --> 00:48:35,092
if you were me,

838
00:48:35,092 --> 00:48:37,098
what would you ask for?

839
00:48:57,198 --> 00:48:58,967
Just like you said,

840
00:48:58,967 --> 00:49:00,856
both of them showed up this morning.

841
00:49:00,856 --> 00:49:03,650
Run the factory full tilt,
three shifts around the clock.

842
00:49:03,650 --> 00:49:05,419
But there's nothing to make.

843
00:49:05,419 --> 00:49:07,571
The lights can't go off in that factory.

844
00:49:07,571 --> 00:49:10,138
The machines need to run to rattle them.

845
00:49:10,138 --> 00:49:12,826
<i>Post job listings on every hiring site,</i>

846
00:49:12,826 --> 00:49:15,858
say you're bringing on a hundred more.

847
00:49:15,858 --> 00:49:17,619
Top-tier salary.

848
00:49:17,619 --> 00:49:18,678
Excuse me?

849
00:49:18,678 --> 00:49:21,623
<i>A desperate Jae Gyeong is going
to throw out around 150 billion.</i>

850
00:49:21,623 --> 00:49:24,629
Don't sign a thing, just hold out.

851
00:49:24,629 --> 00:49:26,795
300 billion in three days.

852
00:49:26,795 --> 00:49:28,967
I'll get your asking price sky-high,

853
00:49:28,967 --> 00:49:31,569
so just stick to the plan.

854
00:49:45,300 --> 00:49:47,877
Good morning, sir.

855
00:49:49,498 --> 00:49:51,266
What the hell?

856
00:49:51,987 --> 00:49:54,292
Something good must have happened, sir.

857
00:49:54,292 --> 00:49:55,917
Your face is glowing like the sun.

858
00:49:55,917 --> 00:49:57,603
Did you bang your head again?

859
00:49:57,603 --> 00:50:00,957
Kang Jae Gyeong looked like death warmed over.

860
00:50:00,957 --> 00:50:03,251
She called an emergency meeting
like everything fell apart.

861
00:50:03,251 --> 00:50:06,134
Running around like crazy.

862
00:50:06,134 --> 00:50:07,842
Emergency meeting?

863
00:50:07,842 --> 00:50:10,218
She's losing it.

864
00:50:10,218 --> 00:50:11,300
But

865
00:50:11,300 --> 00:50:13,403
why are you telling me?

866
00:50:18,009 --> 00:50:19,742
Well...

867
00:50:21,561 --> 00:50:23,700
I'm a fan of yours.

868
00:50:25,176 --> 00:50:27,417
You can do this!

869
00:50:30,028 --> 00:50:32,004
That lunatic.

870
00:50:32,864 --> 00:50:34,924
He's actually nuts, right?

871
00:50:38,495 --> 00:50:41,537
[Choiseong Chemicals President's Office]

872
00:50:41,537 --> 00:50:44,367
I'm acquiring it for 150 billion.

873
00:50:44,367 --> 00:50:47,788
The port project alone is 400 billion,

874
00:50:47,788 --> 00:50:49,336
we have nothing left.

875
00:50:49,336 --> 00:50:51,424
The board will lose their minds.

876
00:50:51,424 --> 00:50:53,635
If they realize this is a power struggle,

877
00:50:53,635 --> 00:50:55,178
your chairmanship itself

878
00:50:55,178 --> 00:50:56,984
could come into question.

879
00:50:56,984 --> 00:50:58,515
So what,

880
00:50:58,515 --> 00:51:00,303
I just walk away?

881
00:51:00,303 --> 00:51:03,793
Do none of you get how much this means to me?

882
00:51:03,793 --> 00:51:05,300
This is your shot

883
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:07,983
at being founding members,

884
00:51:07,983 --> 00:51:09,732
and you don't even see it?

885
00:51:10,803 --> 00:51:14,884
I'll cover the gap
out of my own pocket if I have to,

886
00:51:14,884 --> 00:51:17,091
so redraft the contract,

887
00:51:20,182 --> 00:51:21,981
right now.

888
00:51:29,254 --> 00:51:30,842
[Choiseong Chemicals President's Office]

889
00:51:30,842 --> 00:51:32,565
Ma'am.

890
00:51:37,759 --> 00:51:39,681
<i>I'm not taking your side.</i>

891
00:51:39,681 --> 00:51:41,224
<i>President Kang Jae Gyeong,</i>

892
00:51:41,224 --> 00:51:43,143
<i>you've made a big mistake.</i>

893
00:51:43,143 --> 00:51:45,036
<i>Got it?</i>

894
00:51:45,896 --> 00:51:49,335
He's meeting with CEO Kim right now.

895
00:51:54,717 --> 00:51:55,864
What are you doing?

896
00:51:55,864 --> 00:51:57,574
Dig deeper.

897
00:51:57,574 --> 00:51:59,217
Yes, ma'am.

898
00:52:01,745 --> 00:52:04,071
[Hwang Jun Hyeon]

899
00:52:07,042 --> 00:52:09,689
[Hwang Jun Hyeon]

900
00:52:13,465 --> 00:52:16,056
[Na Byeong Mo]

901
00:52:19,551 --> 00:52:23,892
What brings the president of Choiseong Trading

902
00:52:23,892 --> 00:52:26,953
all the way out here in such busy times?

903
00:52:29,144 --> 00:52:32,035
Please help me out just one more time.

904
00:52:32,035 --> 00:52:34,194
That sly fox Jae Gyeong

905
00:52:34,194 --> 00:52:36,787
had the nerve to bid 150 billion.

906
00:52:36,787 --> 00:52:40,383
We need at least 200 billion
to seal the deal...

907
00:52:42,300 --> 00:52:45,038
You swore you'd buy
the company for 100 billion,

908
00:52:45,038 --> 00:52:47,795
now you want another 100?

909
00:52:47,795 --> 00:52:48,959
Go find

910
00:52:48,959 --> 00:52:52,170
a single place that lends without collateral.

911
00:52:52,170 --> 00:52:55,731
Where do you find the nerve?

912
00:52:58,009 --> 00:53:00,846
The real estate under Construction's name,

913
00:53:00,846 --> 00:53:03,011
I'll put that up.

914
00:53:03,011 --> 00:53:04,036
You know,

915
00:53:04,036 --> 00:53:05,967
my father has tons of land.

916
00:53:05,967 --> 00:53:08,186
Once I close this and take the chair,

917
00:53:08,186 --> 00:53:12,120
I'll hand-pick the prime parcels for you.

918
00:53:12,854 --> 00:53:15,487
Don't wear out those knees while you're young.

919
00:53:15,487 --> 00:53:17,599
You'll pay for it later.

920
00:53:20,297 --> 00:53:21,408
Secretary Jo,

921
00:53:21,408 --> 00:53:23,702
send him off with some pocket money,

922
00:53:23,702 --> 00:53:25,659
whatever he needs.

923
00:53:25,659 --> 00:53:27,205
Thank you.

924
00:53:27,205 --> 00:53:28,848
Thank you.

925
00:53:30,208 --> 00:53:31,482
[GF Solutions, CEO Kim Sang Do]

926
00:53:35,630 --> 00:53:36,798
Hey.

927
00:53:36,798 --> 00:53:39,885
I've matched a price
you'll be more than happy with.

928
00:53:39,885 --> 00:53:42,137
- 150 billion...
<i>- I'm sorry.</i>

929
00:53:42,137 --> 00:53:44,842
Trading is offering 200 billion.

930
00:53:44,842 --> 00:53:46,224
200 billion?

931
00:53:46,224 --> 00:53:48,467
I'd love to go with you

932
00:53:48,467 --> 00:53:50,729
given our history,

933
00:53:50,729 --> 00:53:53,831
but it's a tough spot.

934
00:53:54,566 --> 00:53:58,336
So, I'll be waiting for a better offer.

935
00:54:01,759 --> 00:54:03,466
Secretary Yeo.

936
00:54:05,176 --> 00:54:07,259
How much can we pull from Siren?

937
00:54:07,259 --> 00:54:09,539
President Kang Jae Seong already caught on,

938
00:54:09,539 --> 00:54:11,008
touching it now is too risky.

939
00:54:11,008 --> 00:54:13,067
Stick to the plan.

940
00:54:13,067 --> 00:54:15,420
Liquidate Siren's real estate too.

941
00:54:15,420 --> 00:54:18,397
Once I'm chair, I'll fix it all.

942
00:54:23,717 --> 00:54:24,721
[2026 GF Solutions New Hire Recruitment]
Next applicant.

943
00:54:24,721 --> 00:54:26,511
- Please come in.
- Yes.

944
00:54:26,511 --> 00:54:27,516
[Interview Room]

945
00:54:27,516 --> 00:54:28,979
[2026 GF Solutions
New Hire Recruitment Interview Stage]

946
00:55:01,341 --> 00:55:03,842
[GF Solutions]

947
00:55:05,762 --> 00:55:07,302
[GF Solutions]

948
00:55:07,302 --> 00:55:10,019
[CEO Kim Sang Do]
All right, next bid.

949
00:55:10,019 --> 00:55:11,036
[Chemicals]
210 billion.

950
00:55:11,036 --> 00:55:12,616
Where's the money from?

951
00:55:12,616 --> 00:55:14,955
She got it from the Siren fund.

952
00:55:14,955 --> 00:55:17,835
Then GF is mine.

953
00:55:17,835 --> 00:55:20,717
[Trading]
220 billion, I'm buying.

954
00:55:20,717 --> 00:55:22,316
You can't, sir.

955
00:55:22,316 --> 00:55:23,989
I took out a loan.

956
00:55:23,989 --> 00:55:25,987
That one's mine.

957
00:55:25,987 --> 00:55:27,091
[Chemicals]
240 billion.

958
00:55:27,091 --> 00:55:27,951
Chemicals, 240 billion.

959
00:55:27,951 --> 00:55:30,052
[Trading]
260 billion.

960
00:55:30,717 --> 00:55:32,847
Trading, 260.

961
00:55:33,675 --> 00:55:35,542
[Chemicals]
280 billion.

962
00:55:35,542 --> 00:55:36,626
Chemicals, 280.

963
00:55:36,626 --> 00:55:38,134
[Trading]
290 billion.

964
00:55:38,134 --> 00:55:40,897
No, 300 billion.

965
00:55:43,425 --> 00:55:46,110
President Kang Jae Seong!

966
00:55:48,592 --> 00:55:50,432
Sold!

967
00:55:50,432 --> 00:55:53,076
Hey, Jae Seong!

968
00:55:54,060 --> 00:55:55,161
Are you crazy?

969
00:55:55,161 --> 00:55:57,259
If the price keeps shooting up,

970
00:55:57,259 --> 00:55:58,981
we're the ones who lose, you know.

971
00:55:58,981 --> 00:56:00,897
I don't care about losses.

972
00:56:00,897 --> 00:56:02,527
I just need to beat you.

973
00:56:02,527 --> 00:56:03,686
What,

974
00:56:03,686 --> 00:56:05,235
burned through the slush fund?

975
00:56:05,235 --> 00:56:07,218
Should've skimmed more.

976
00:56:07,218 --> 00:56:10,994
Or married rich like I did.

977
00:56:10,994 --> 00:56:12,967
This money,

978
00:56:12,967 --> 00:56:14,931
is it Taeha's?

979
00:56:16,176 --> 00:56:17,709
My father-in-law

980
00:56:17,709 --> 00:56:20,342
is so bitter about the port deal,

981
00:56:20,342 --> 00:56:22,674
he opened the vault.

982
00:56:22,674 --> 00:56:25,108
You can't beat me on this.

983
00:56:25,108 --> 00:56:26,551
I'll bid 10 billion

984
00:56:26,551 --> 00:56:30,554
more than you, every time.

985
00:56:30,554 --> 00:56:33,138
I told you, don't trust him.

986
00:56:33,138 --> 00:56:34,459
Forget Father's words?

987
00:56:34,459 --> 00:56:37,787
Since when do you listen to him?

988
00:56:38,509 --> 00:56:40,748
You tried to kill him.

989
00:56:41,759 --> 00:56:43,488
Watch it.

990
00:56:43,488 --> 00:56:45,461
Hey.

991
00:56:46,550 --> 00:56:49,509
You're in this too.

992
00:56:49,509 --> 00:56:52,718
Don't get fresh with me.

993
00:56:56,051 --> 00:56:58,558
Nice try, little sis.

994
00:57:00,313 --> 00:57:01,759
I'm off

995
00:57:01,759 --> 00:57:04,464
to buy GF Solutions,

996
00:57:04,464 --> 00:57:08,468
if you want to hand
the port deal over, let me know.

997
00:57:08,468 --> 00:57:10,778
Got it?

998
00:57:27,092 --> 00:57:30,574
This is what happens
when you doubt me and stir up a mess.

999
00:57:30,574 --> 00:57:33,163
You lost GF Solutions for nothing.

1000
00:57:33,163 --> 00:57:34,202
Shut up.

1001
00:57:34,202 --> 00:57:35,954
Don't mess with me.

1002
00:57:35,954 --> 00:57:38,014
Want my help?

1003
00:57:38,665 --> 00:57:41,225
I can stop this.

1004
00:57:42,989 --> 00:57:43,993
Don't be ridiculous.

1005
00:57:43,993 --> 00:57:45,133
You couldn't.

1006
00:57:45,133 --> 00:57:48,342
So Choiseong doesn't matter to you.

1007
00:57:48,342 --> 00:57:51,425
You don't really want the chair.

1008
00:57:51,425 --> 00:57:52,762
I'll head

1009
00:57:52,762 --> 00:57:55,948
to Jae Seong, who actually wants me.

1010
00:57:58,393 --> 00:58:00,176
A way,

1011
00:58:00,176 --> 00:58:01,996
you really have one?

1012
00:58:03,857 --> 00:58:06,265
You know what I can do.

1013
00:58:10,176 --> 00:58:12,381
Help me.

1014
00:58:12,381 --> 00:58:14,493
If you help me this once,

1015
00:58:14,493 --> 00:58:16,719
I'll never forget it.

1016
00:58:17,913 --> 00:58:19,873
Apologize first.

1017
00:58:19,873 --> 00:58:21,553
I helped you, and you doubted me,

1018
00:58:21,553 --> 00:58:24,461
got rough, had me tailed.

1019
00:58:24,461 --> 00:58:27,807
Apologize properly, and I'll reconsider.

1020
00:58:44,634 --> 00:58:47,717
I'm truly sorry,

1021
00:58:47,717 --> 00:58:49,585
Mr. Hwang.

1022
00:58:57,051 --> 00:58:58,370
Jae Gyeong

1023
00:58:58,370 --> 00:59:00,638
bowed her head.

1024
00:59:09,052 --> 00:59:12,191
You have the 300 billion?

1025
00:59:13,509 --> 00:59:15,053
Let's go,

1026
00:59:15,053 --> 00:59:17,155
buy GF Solutions.

1027
00:59:27,092 --> 00:59:29,218
I'm here

1028
00:59:29,218 --> 00:59:31,403
with 300 billion.

1029
00:59:31,403 --> 00:59:35,089
Three hundred billion...

1030
00:59:35,759 --> 00:59:37,592
Won...

1031
00:59:41,663 --> 00:59:42,918
[CEO Kim Sang Do]

1032
00:59:44,051 --> 00:59:45,850
Sir?

1033
00:59:48,833 --> 00:59:50,134
[Corporate Acquisition Contract]

1034
00:59:50,134 --> 00:59:52,815
The terms are as stated.

1035
00:59:53,637 --> 00:59:55,886
The 30 percent stake

1036
00:59:55,886 --> 00:59:59,530
is excluded from this deal.

1037
01:00:00,390 --> 01:00:03,059
What does this mean?

1038
01:00:03,059 --> 01:00:06,082
It's CEO Kim's special condition.

1039
01:00:06,082 --> 01:00:07,981
You never said that before.

1040
01:00:07,981 --> 01:00:09,902
Thirty percent is absurd.

1041
01:00:09,902 --> 01:00:12,293
Whose stake even is this?

1042
01:00:13,566 --> 01:00:15,228
Is it yours, CEO Kim?

1043
01:00:15,228 --> 01:00:17,240
If you want to walk away now,

1044
01:00:17,240 --> 01:00:18,533
go ahead.

1045
01:00:18,533 --> 01:00:20,118
President Kang Jae Seong

1046
01:00:20,118 --> 01:00:23,137
is dying to buy on these terms.

1047
01:00:25,592 --> 01:00:27,809
What's your call?

1048
01:00:28,926 --> 01:00:31,145
Do you agree?

1049
01:00:34,049 --> 01:00:35,091
[President Kang Jae Seong, Choiseong Trading]

1050
01:00:35,091 --> 01:00:37,218
Goodness.

1051
01:00:37,218 --> 01:00:38,971
Unbelievable.

1052
01:00:38,971 --> 01:00:42,073
It's President Kang Jae Seong...

1053
01:00:49,884 --> 01:00:51,416
I...

1054
01:00:54,842 --> 01:00:56,587
agree.

1055
01:00:58,240 --> 01:00:59,425
Yes,

1056
01:00:59,425 --> 01:01:01,092
same here.

1057
01:01:02,911 --> 01:01:06,665
Then sign.

1058
01:01:06,665 --> 01:01:09,330
<i>I'll buy the 30 percent later.</i>

1059
01:01:09,330 --> 01:01:13,020
<i>Right now, GF Solutions comes first.</i>

1060
01:01:16,591 --> 01:01:21,532
[Acquirer: Choiseong Chemicals,
Kang Jae Gyeong]

1061
01:01:25,385 --> 01:01:28,895
A fortune just landed in your lap.

1062
01:01:28,895 --> 01:01:31,940
How is this even possible?

1063
01:01:31,940 --> 01:01:34,041
I can't believe it.

1064
01:01:35,009 --> 01:01:37,253
Thank you.

1065
01:01:38,550 --> 01:01:40,840
It was a solid deal.

1066
01:01:42,638 --> 01:01:45,134
Your company was worth every won.

1067
01:01:45,134 --> 01:01:47,539
The 30 percent stake,

1068
01:01:47,539 --> 01:01:50,185
who do I send it to?

1069
01:01:50,185 --> 01:01:52,852
Smile Investment.

1070
01:02:01,494 --> 01:02:03,138
Whatever you want,

1071
01:02:03,138 --> 01:02:05,531
just name it, Mr. Hwang.

1072
01:02:07,259 --> 01:02:10,634
Your Choiseong Trading shares,

1073
01:02:10,634 --> 01:02:12,176
I'd like those.

1074
01:02:12,176 --> 01:02:14,395
One percent.

1075
01:02:14,395 --> 01:02:15,692
One percent?

1076
01:02:15,692 --> 01:02:17,527
Why Trading shares?

1077
01:02:17,527 --> 01:02:21,194
Chemicals will soar once I take over.

1078
01:02:21,194 --> 01:02:23,800
I want to run Trading someday.

1079
01:02:25,092 --> 01:02:26,803
What?

1080
01:02:27,967 --> 01:02:29,309
Do you think I can't?

1081
01:02:29,309 --> 01:02:30,957
I think you can.

1082
01:02:30,957 --> 01:02:33,348
Honestly, you surprised me.

1083
01:02:33,348 --> 01:02:35,728
I didn't expect this.

1084
01:02:36,581 --> 01:02:38,176
I'm starting

1085
01:02:38,176 --> 01:02:40,258
to want you on my side.

1086
01:02:40,258 --> 01:02:42,469
Badly.

1087
01:02:42,469 --> 01:02:46,030
Now that's the look of real trust.

1088
01:02:46,941 --> 01:02:49,214
Come work for me.

1089
01:02:49,214 --> 01:02:52,354
Make me chair of Choiseong,

1090
01:02:52,354 --> 01:02:54,956
and Chemicals is yours.

1091
01:02:57,926 --> 01:03:00,176
I'll think about it,

1092
01:03:00,176 --> 01:03:02,171
seriously.

1093
01:03:02,800 --> 01:03:05,032
Leaving already?

1094
01:03:05,032 --> 01:03:06,785
The party's just starting.

1095
01:03:06,785 --> 01:03:08,952
I have to pack.

1096
01:03:08,952 --> 01:03:11,272
I took some time off.

1097
01:03:11,272 --> 01:03:12,452
Where to?

1098
01:03:12,452 --> 01:03:14,413
Somewhere with great mountains.

1099
01:03:14,413 --> 01:03:16,878
What do they call it now?

1100
01:03:16,878 --> 01:03:18,176
A hot...

1101
01:03:18,176 --> 01:03:19,992
hotspot?

1102
01:03:19,992 --> 01:03:22,859
It's a sizzling place.

1103
01:03:54,830 --> 01:03:56,790
Did your father send for me?

1104
01:03:56,790 --> 01:03:57,836
Or what,

1105
01:03:57,836 --> 01:04:00,134
is he saying to dump

1106
01:04:00,134 --> 01:04:01,231
your idiot husband?

1107
01:04:01,231 --> 01:04:04,358
If you were that scared,
you shouldn't have lost this one.

1108
01:04:05,250 --> 01:04:06,810
You're right.

1109
01:04:06,810 --> 01:04:09,510
A loser like me should just die.

1110
01:04:09,510 --> 01:04:11,031
I don't deserve to live.

1111
01:04:11,031 --> 01:04:12,867
I'm not worth a drink...

1112
01:04:13,894 --> 01:04:16,497
Ouch, that hurts!

1113
01:04:16,497 --> 01:04:18,640
Are you not stopping me?

1114
01:04:20,190 --> 01:04:21,818
CEO Kim

1115
01:04:21,818 --> 01:04:23,528
was almost mine.

1116
01:04:23,528 --> 01:04:26,156
One signature and it was done,

1117
01:04:26,156 --> 01:04:28,717
then Jae Gyeong pulled some trick,

1118
01:04:28,717 --> 01:04:30,592
and the whole deal flipped.

1119
01:04:30,592 --> 01:04:32,662
I'm losing my mind!

1120
01:04:32,662 --> 01:04:35,454
That's your problem right there.

1121
01:04:35,454 --> 01:04:38,668
You've never once beaten her fair and square,

1122
01:04:38,668 --> 01:04:41,646
and you still won't fight dirty.

1123
01:04:42,425 --> 01:04:44,545
Who said play fair?

1124
01:04:44,545 --> 01:04:47,550
If you can't win, find dirt and blackmail her.

1125
01:04:47,550 --> 01:04:51,364
That cold-blooded woman has no weak spot...

1126
01:04:56,009 --> 01:04:57,912
There is one.

1127
01:04:58,634 --> 01:05:00,415
A weakness.

1128
01:05:02,967 --> 01:05:05,086
Jae Gyeong

1129
01:05:07,259 --> 01:05:09,757
tried to kill our father.

1130
01:05:12,717 --> 01:05:15,221
Tell me everything.

1131
01:05:16,009 --> 01:05:18,057
I need to hear this.

1132
01:05:29,837 --> 01:05:32,572
The view is something else.

1133
01:05:33,265 --> 01:05:36,909
No wonder Father couldn't leave this seat.

1134
01:05:43,051 --> 01:05:45,383
Sit here long enough,

1135
01:05:45,383 --> 01:05:48,337
and you'd grow ambitious too.

1136
01:05:49,592 --> 01:05:52,717
Wouldn't you, Director Lee?

1137
01:05:53,425 --> 01:05:56,137
That depends on the person.

1138
01:05:57,176 --> 01:05:59,666
Then I'll close out the succession

1139
01:05:59,666 --> 01:06:02,018
at the next board meeting.

1140
01:06:08,342 --> 01:06:11,970
Where should I

1141
01:06:11,970 --> 01:06:14,614
reassign righteous you?

1142
01:06:21,717 --> 01:06:23,300
<i>Welcome aboard, everyone.</i>

1143
01:06:23,300 --> 01:06:25,275
<i>This is Hankuk Airlines Flight 747,</i>

1144
01:06:25,275 --> 01:06:28,383
<i>bound for Yulivia.</i>

1145
01:06:28,383 --> 01:06:31,031
<i>Flight time to Yulivia</i>

1146
01:06:31,031 --> 01:06:32,759
<i>is 14 hours and 30 minutes.</i>

1147
01:06:32,759 --> 01:06:34,910
<i>Further announcements</i>

1148
01:06:34,910 --> 01:06:38,450
<i>will follow from our crew shortly.</i>

1149
01:06:38,450 --> 01:06:40,550
<i>We'll do our very best to make your trip</i>

1150
01:06:40,550 --> 01:06:42,042
[These are the documents you requested]
<i>safe and comfortable.</i>

1151
01:06:42,042 --> 01:06:43,675
<i>Thank you.</i>

1152
01:06:43,675 --> 01:06:46,213
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, welcome aboard.</i>

1153
01:06:46,213 --> 01:06:52,135
<i>This is Korea Airway 747 bound for Yulivia.</i>

1154
01:06:52,135 --> 01:06:53,569
[Major Lithium Reserves in Yulivia]

1155
01:06:56,306 --> 01:06:58,507
[Kang Jae Gyeong]

1156
01:06:59,559 --> 01:07:01,702
Yes, President Kang.

1157
01:07:02,854 --> 01:07:05,045
Have a great vacation.

1158
01:07:05,045 --> 01:07:07,234
When you return,

1159
01:07:07,234 --> 01:07:10,845
I'll be chair of Choiseong,
so don't be shocked.

1160
01:07:10,845 --> 01:07:13,240
Then I'll prepare a little surprise.

1161
01:07:13,240 --> 01:07:15,251
I can't wait

1162
01:07:15,251 --> 01:07:17,911
to see what it is.

1163
01:07:17,911 --> 01:07:20,221
You should be excited.

1164
01:07:21,091 --> 01:07:23,516
I'll blow your mind.

1165
01:08:08,467 --> 01:08:09,504
<i>I came to warn you.</i>

1166
01:08:09,504 --> 01:08:11,737
<i>To show what happens when you cross Choiseong.</i>

1167
01:08:11,737 --> 01:08:13,736
<i>Look at Mr. Choiseong.</i>

1168
01:08:13,736 --> 01:08:16,057
<i>The Team 2 contract is ours, period.</i>

1169
01:08:16,057 --> 01:08:18,436
<i>You know Na Byeong Mo's shady.</i>

1170
01:08:18,436 --> 01:08:20,052
<i>I need to break him.</i>

1171
01:08:20,052 --> 01:08:22,029
<i>Jae Gyeong's secretary was
behind the port deal.</i>

1172
01:08:22,029 --> 01:08:23,259
<i>Hwang Jun Hyeon.</i>

1173
01:08:23,259 --> 01:08:25,249
<i>I told you to bring me something
for my heartburn.</i>

1174
01:08:25,249 --> 01:08:26,813
<i>Find the right moment,</i>

1175
01:08:26,813 --> 01:08:28,209
<i>and we take them down in one shot.</i>

1176
01:08:28,209 --> 01:08:31,383
<i>If you'll back me as the next chair...</i>

1177
01:08:31,383 --> 01:08:32,509
<i>Mother.</i>

1178
01:08:32,509 --> 01:08:35,249
<i>Now happiness is all that's left for us.</i>

1179
01:08:35,249 --> 01:08:38,074
<i>If I don't do it, someone else will.</i>

1180
01:08:38,074 --> 01:08:39,242
<i>Bang Geul,</i>

1181
01:08:39,242 --> 01:08:42,053
<i>what do we do about your father?</i>
